Signs have two functions: significative (objective) and expressive (subjective) ones.
Significative: The sign means something that the observer can readily interpret, thanks to a shared semiotic system, like language.
Expressive: The observer can add meaning depending on the way the sign is expressed, focusing on its context, as well.
Take a conversation: the observer can understand the content of the speaker’s communication using language.

Signs have two functions: significative (objective) and expressive (subjective) ones.
Significative: The sign means something that the observer can readily interpret, thanks to a shared semiotic system, like language.
Expressive: The observer can add meaning depending on the way the sign is expressed, focusing on its context, as well.
Take a conversation: the observer can understand the content of the speaker’s communication using language.
But the you also can add another layer of interpretation based upon what they know about the speaker and the situation in which the speaker speaks.
